01 – Asset Identification

This phase establishes the foundation of the risk management process by identifying and cataloging Business Supplies, Inc.’s (BSI) critical information assets.

The objective of this phase is to:
	•	Identify key information assets that support business operations
	•	Document asset ownership, data types, and business value
	•	Support downstream threat modeling and risk analysis activities

Asset identification enables risk based decision making by ensuring that security and governance efforts are aligned to assets with the highest business impact.
